article.headline: Oklahoma 67, Colorado 60
article.story: NORMAN, Okla. -- Cade Davis had 15 points and four other Oklahoma players scored in double figures as the Sooners defeated Colorado 67-60 Saturday. Andrew Fitzgerald, Carl Blair Jr., and Cameron Clark each added 13 points for Oklahoma (10-9, 2/3 Big 12). Steven Pledger had 11. Alec Burks and Cory Higgins scored 15 points apiece to lead the Buffaloes (14-6, 3-2), who have lost 24 straight in Norman. The Sooners went on a 13-4 run to take at a 32-26 lead into halftime, and they then scored the first five points of the second half to push their lead to 11. Colorado rallied to tie it at 52 with 3:25 remaining, but Oklahoma pulled away by making 13-of-16 free throws down the stretch.
